    <sec id="s3d">
      <title>Usage</title>
      <p>The WoRMS web service is being used by at least 28 organisations from 12 countries (<xref ref-type="table" rid="pone-0051629-t008">Table 8</xref>). Permission is not required to use the Web service so there may be additional users we are not aware of. Copies of the database have been licensed out to 61 organisations in 21 countries (<xref ref-type="table" rid="pone-0051629-t009">Table 9</xref>) with demand growing steadily (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="pone-0051629-g004">Figure 4</xref>). Since 2007, all website-use metrics show a steady increase in access (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="pone-0051629-g005">Figure 5</xref>). There were about 600,000 unique visitors in 2011, and 57,000 in December 2011 alone, and on average &gt;3,000 unique visitors per day (based on IP addresses). This represents over 3 million hits per month. Google scholar (24 April 2012) found over 800 citations for “World Register of Marine Species” and that it was cited in over 100 publications.</p>
